,Recommended,214970,17109694,"Posted: 18 July, 2015",all,Evaheist,"This game plays very similar to games like Capsized where you control the 360 degrees direction of your shooting with the mouse and control your character's movement with the keyboard. Unlike Capsized, though, it's actually a very fun title despite its absurd difficulty and challenge. It's also physics based so you'll need to think about your jump momentums as well as different items around the area which can be thrown around by gunfire or more hazardous means. You'll get to mount animals and mechs and fight enemy mechs in glorious and epic boss fights.The only let-down may be the high difficulty of this game even on normal which can really put a barrier on progression. Each level cleared feels like a real accomplishment.I wouldn't believe you if you said an action game made with flash can be as beautiful, complex and challenging as this but now that I've experienced it, I truly appreciate the work behind this game. Recommended, if you're not easily overwhelmed by challenge."
