,Recommended,214970,8588549,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,Jakkar,"This game is one of the finest interactive examples of what it means to be truly Awesome, with a capital A.A labour of love created with unparalelled attention-to-detail in a platformer, partnered with well-tuned physics that make every fight unique, no matter how many times repeated.Wild 80s science-fiction, heavy on the action, low on the subtlety. Ride direwolves while firing double-barrelled machineguns at giant leaping robotic quadrupeds with bladed whips forty feet long for tails. To exactly the kind of music you'd imagine partnering with that image. A bizarre fusion of intense physics-based action platforming, the adult form of the clunky, old-fashioned Contra or Metal Slug games, and high-challenge Japanese bullet hell boss battles, without ever being anything less than exciting.A short but intensely satisfying experience even I can replay. I have trouble with *finishing* most games before I grow bored. This one has the freshness of a randomised experience, despite the hand-crafted levels, courtesy of the rich variety a physics-enabled world provides. Rely upon it to continually surprise you with a higher level of intensity, all the way to the end.I've honestly never played a better shooter-platformer - Aleksey Abramenko is the new king of the genre."
