,Recommended,214970,1925939,"Posted: 21 January, 2013",all,DrBrogbo,"This is an interesting game. It was done completely by 1 guy, which is impressive, the art style is interesting (if a little goofy at times), and the music can be pretty driving until you've heard them loop a dozen times.The boss fights are pretty cool, except they are basically impossible the first time through. You will lose repeatedly until you figure out the bosses' patterns.This may be the generally accepted mechanic for games like this, but I've always found it frustrating.The levels are very well-done, and are noticeably different each time. There are even little mini-levels where you're sliding down a snow-covered slope, which are a blast.The controls are serviceable with a 360 controller, and I've heard they're good with keyboard+mouse too. Sometimes, though, they genuinely get in the way, and the way the wolf moves is inherently weird. It works, though.The game is also rather short. I enjoyed it for the most part (other than dying 20+ times in the final boss alone. Frustrating to the max), but it's fun if you enjoy mindless side-scrolling shooters.The game is at it's best when you are frantically trying to dodge one enemy's bullets while shooting another. It's at it's worst when you're trying to time precision jumps or dodge boss projectiles, and the controls get in the way.If you use a 360 controller, I STRONGLY recommend you unbind the jump key from the analog stick, or you'll be jumping over and over and over and over and over when you never wanted to. I used LB instead, and left RB to cycle through weapons."
