76561198024556517,Recommended,214970,7789581,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,MiloticMaster,"P.S Dont mind the hrs on record- I left the game on in the background.Lets get this out of the way- the game has physics. Those kinds of physics that make boxes fly everywhere when you shoot them. This is might make/break this game for you. On one hand- you'll love when you balance those boxes just right to climb over an obstacle or use as improvised cover. On the other hand you're going to hate when you lose health after being hit by a random box, or when you cant collect a pickup or activate something because a box is ontop of it. I personally, think it adds to the game. The game is designed around it, with the right weapons and keeping an eye on your surrondings you can use the physics to your advantage. It also adds a degree of random to the game so you're always thinking on your toes.As for the rest of the game; it plays like a modern Contra with a dash of amazing. Challenging, a variety of weapons, epic bosses. Mech suits, Wolves you can ride on, a health bar, animations based on physics, depleting ammo and EPIC BOSSES! Truly some of the best boss design Ive ever seen. Its Run n Gun to the power of awesome. If the physics dont put you off- I strongly recommend you at least try it. It has a demo."
