,Recommended,214970,35015322,Posted: 16 September,all,ProfJimbo,"Okay, so I managed to finish this game. I tried using a Rock Candy controller first but cursor aiming was too hard, so I used a mouse and keyboard which was okay. This game is a flash game which I usually try to avoid, which is hard to without any tag for flash-based. Anyhow, how to rate this game.Graphically, the animations are loose joint kind, like there seems to be strings holding up characters.  Not alot of bright colors, which for a military type game is normal, and at 1080p textures and outlines are slightly dull. Backgrounds are the slightly blurred effect type-for an off in the distance effect.Gameplay, is going to depend on finding a good controller or mouse and keyboard. My keyboard is the normal big desktop kind; it has very squishy keys with slippery surfaces.  Anyhow, the main character has a floaty jump, and its height is affected by various factors: like unsteady ground or surfaces, carrying heavy guns, riding mech, jumping direction, springy objects like floatsom on water and tree branches and low ceiling of courese etc.  Aiming cursor is a big yellowish triangle, It is still easy to lose track of said cursor because the whole screen is targetable-not at the same time of course. But there is an particles gun that can pass through certain walls and objects and can target multiple enemies in a straight line. Besides riding a big Wolf that can squish slash enemies, there are mechs: grappling hook mech which grabs and throws barrels and light debris. Gun mech with sword and another combination mech with missiles. Enemies include standard unarmored to armored soldiers, mech riders, dragons that shoot, grab and or use a knife tail, wolves, fire-spewing balloons etc. Physics allow using barrels, rocks, snow, and expanding goo jars for defense, offense or for climbing. So there is lots of fun to be had experimenting there for fun of strategy.Bosses are good variety, flying grabbers, wild girl robot with elemental and gun weapons, and Mace the last boss. The last boss took me about 15 hours, but I kept getting stuck in debris or knocked off the edges. Finally, managed to get some pointers online, but I was lucky and memorization helped with getting ready for last boss phases.Decent game, and perhaps original, well, original from my experiences with these run and gun games. Game is short if the last boss does not phase you.If I had to make improvement suggestions I say: 1) make custom cursor color available-the last boss was same color as cursor. 2) on last boss the main character's waist to feet are cut off by camera and also when jumping off elevated stands the bottom of screen is cut off.I had alot of trouble with the debris piling up, sometimes getting hit by a barrel and flying off ledge. I finally just managed to quickly learn how to aim ahead of the giant enemy last boss and take off health quickly, especially at the beginning phase, still debris could help by blocking homing missles so its up to player preference."
